<dl id="n11139l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11139l">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11139l"> 139(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> his reins <font face="wake">T</font> to <font face="wake">I</font> <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n11139l"><li>FW 533.10 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n11139l">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n11139l">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n11139l">MS BL 47482b-105</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:077 <a name="rA2yd" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rB0yd">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/rB0yd.htm#n11139l">Draft: III&sect;3B.0+</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"> <b>Le Drame</b> Rassurez-vous, mon enfant; celui qui sonde <mark>les reins</mark> et les coeurs vous jugera sur vos intentions, qui &eacute;taient pures, et non sur votre action qui est condamnable. <br:<font color="green">[Be reassured, my child. He who searches loins and hearts will judge you by your intentions, that were pure, rather than by your action, that was blameworthy.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Atala</i> 68-9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
